################################################################################
##### HAUPTKNOTEN ##############################################################
################################################################################

@NODE INTRO "PolyEd À Concepts"

Welcome to PolyEd
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

PolyEd is one of the most user friendly text editors for the Amiga.
It is kept small and easy, but has all the features.

PolyEd has all features, needed to edit texts, but no other features,
like clocks, memory displays, calculators ...

As the Amiga has a great multitasking operating system, it is, in my
opinion unnecessary to put all those things into one single program, 
but better to set up one's desired environment by some different
programs (which can be further improved by arexx).

In other words, if you need a calculator, parallel to PolyEd, why not
run the one from the 'utilities' drawer or one from the public domain
pool.

Via the arexx-port, centering, formating and functions you can think
of, can be added to PolyEd too.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE WHAT_SYSTEM "PolyEd À System requirements"

System requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

PolyEd runs on all Amigas with operating system OS 2.0 or higher, and
also supports the new functions of OS2.1 and OS3.0 like localizing,
AGA chips etc.

PolyEd can be run with 512 kB and one floppy disk drive, but of course
it is better to have more memory and a hard disk. PolyEd has been
tested sucessfully on Amiga 1200 (where it has been developed) and
Amiga 4000/030 with OS3.0.
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE INSTALL "PolyEd À Installation"

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~

Installation is done via the Commodore Installer (not included in
this package). Simply double-click the 'Install' icon and follow the
instructions. The installation is only available in english (which
should not bother you, as you are reading the english documentation
too).

If the Commodore Installer is not available for you, you can install
PolyEd by hand quite easily:

  a) Drag the PolyEd-Drawer (or Disk) into the Drawer, where you want
     to install PolyEd (e.g. "Workbench:Tools") and drop it there.
     Now the Workbench will copy PolyEd to the selected drawer.

  b) Add the following lines to the file 's:user-startup' (use the
     real path instead of <path to PolyEd> e.g. "Workbench:Tools/PolyEd").
	
       Assign PED: <path to PolyEd>
       Path PED: Add

  c) To save disk-space, you can delete the documentations and
     catalogs  of languages you do not use.

@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE FEATURES "PolyEd À Features"

PolyEd provides the following Features
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

@{" À Easy to use                                    " Link FEATURES_EASY_TO_USE}
@{" À Editing any number of texts simultaneous       " Link FEATURES_MULTI_TEXTS}
@{" À Any number of windows per text                 " Link FEATURES_MULTI_WINDOWS}
@{" À Unlimited Undo/Redo (almost)                   " Link FEATURES_UNDO_REDO}
@{" À Context-sensitive help                         " Link FEATURES_HELP}
@{" À Supports OS 2.0, 2.1 and 3.0                   " Link FEATURES_OS_SUPPORT}
@{" À Different languages (OS 2.1 or higher)         " Link FEATURES_LOCALE}

@{" À Supports the clipboard                         " Link FEATURES_CLIPBOARD}
@{" À Supports all screen-modes                      " Link FEATURES_SCREENMODES}
@{" À nonmodal requesters                            " Link FEATURES_NONMODAL_REQUESTERS}
@{" À Macros                                         " Link FEATURES_MACROS}
@{" À ARexx-Port                                     " Link FEATURES_AREXX}
@{" À and lots more                                  " Link FEATURES_ETC}
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE STARTUP "PolyEd À Getting started"

Getting started
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

PoyEd can be started from workbench or shell. In both cases files may
be passed, which are then opened automatically. You may also specify
on which screen PolyEd shall be opened and some other things.

Via Environment Variables, you can define the size and position at
which the text-windows will be opened.

@{" Starting from workbench " Link STARTUP_WB}
@{" Starting from the shell " Link STARTUP_SHELL}
@{" Environment Variables   " LINK STARTUP_ENVIRONMENT}

@ENDNODE #######################################################################

@NODE EDIT "PolyEd À Editing texts"

Editing texts
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

PolyEd allows to write and edit texts of arbitrary length with lines
up to 10,000 characters. It is made for editing non-formated texts
like programs etc. Being a editor and not a desktop-publishing
prgram, PolyEd doesn't provide different text styles or layout
functions.

@{" Enter and correct text     " LINK EDIT_EDIT}	How to edit texts
@{" Moving the cursor          " LINK CURSOR_MOVEMENT}	How to move the cursor
@{" Block operations           " LINK EDIT_BLOCKS}	Copy, Cut, Paste...
@{" Text windows               " LINK TEXTVIEWS}	Where to edit texts
@ENDNODE ######################################################################

@NODE MENU_TOC "PolyEd À Menus"

The Menus of PolyEd
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Most of PolyEd's functions can be executed via menus.

@{" Project             " Link "MENU_PROJECT"}	open, save, print texts
@{" Edit                " Link "MENU_EDIT"}	copy, cut, paste texts
@{" Search              " Link "MENU_SEARCH"}	find and replace strings
@{" Windows             " Link "MENU_WINDOWS"}	arranging the windows
@{" Macros              " Link "MENU_MACROS"}	learning and managing macros
@{" Settings            " Link "MENU_SETTINGS"}	adapt the editor to your wishes
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

#last change: 15.1.95 rbr
@NODE REQUESTERS "PolyEd À Requesters"

Requesters
~~~~~~~~~~

Requesters are all the little windows which are no text windows. You
can communicate with PolyEd via the requesters. As far as possible
they are non-modal, so they do not lock other windows, while they are
opened.

Besides the requesters for opening and saving texts, settings and
macros, PolyEd provides these requesters:

@{" Reveal                " Link REQUESTER_REVEAL}	Reveal hidden windows
@{" Find                  " Link REQUESTER_FIND}	Find patterns
@{" Find & Replace        " Link REQUESTER_FINDREPLACE}	Find and replace patterns
@{" Go to line            " Link REQUESTER_LINE}	Go to specified line
@{" Assign Macro          " Link REQUESTER_MACROASSIGN}	Assign Macro to a key
@{" Select Macro          " Link REQUESTER_MACROSELECT}	Selection of a macro
@{" Open own Screen       " Link REQUESTER_SCREEN}	Select screenmode for own screen
@{" Miscellanous          " Link REQUESTER_EDSETTINGS}	misc. settings
@{" Select Font           " Link REQUESTER_FONT}	Select font
@{" Colors                " Link REQUESTER_COLORS}	Adjust colors
@ENDNODE #######################################################################

#last change: 13.3.95
@NODE REGISTRATE "PolyEd À Registration"

Registration - or how to get the full version
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

PolyEd is SHAREWARE. This means, that you have to pay me some money,
if you use it frequently. You will get then the newest version of
PolyEd without the shareware limitations.

To get the full version, best fill out the @{"Registration Form" Link REGISTER_FORM} (can be
printed directly from MultiView) and send it to me along with $20.- or
DM 30.-.

I will send you then a disk with the latest version of PolyEd and a
(wunderful) certificate.

Updates ?
~~~~~~~~~

Updates are for free, and available via AmiNet and PD disks. These
updates are full versions for registrated users.

@ENDNODE #######################################################################

